harpless follows the money that ICE funnels into local jails, private contractors, and charter jets, exposing a sprawling system of immigration enforcement that detains and abuses noncitizens at scale. Woven with the wider context of Abdulahi's and Sa'id's stories, this immigration odyssey reveals disturbing truths about Somalia, asylum, and the U.S. court system. Shackled will galvanize readers—attorneys, activists, policymakers, and scholars alike—to call out and dismantle this brutal infrastructure.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aDeportationzUnited StatesvCase studies. 0aDeportationzUnited States. 0aEmigration and immigration lawzUnited States. 0aSomalisxLegal status, laws, etc.zUnited StatesvCase studies. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Emigration & Immigration.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2024z978311079135840uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520390959?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520390959423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520390959/original  a978-3-11-079135-8  University of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2024b2024  aEBA_EMB  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles